{"id":"2009.04025","submitter":"Evan Bauer","authors":"Evan B. Bauer, Josiah Schwab, Lars Bildsten, Sihao Cheng","title":"Multi-Gigayear White Dwarf Cooling Delays from Clustering-Enhanced\n  Gravitational Sedimentation","comments":"23 pages, 14 figures, accepted for publication in ApJ","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.3847/1538-4357/abb5a5","report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph.SR astro-ph.GA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Cooling white dwarfs (WDs) can yield accurate ages when theoretical cooling\nmodels fully account for the physics of the dense plasma of WD interiors. We\nuse MESA to investigate cooling models for a set of massive and ultra-massive\nWDs (0.9-1.3 $M_\\odot$) for which previous models fail to match kinematic age\nindicators based on Gaia DR2. We find that the WDs in this population can be\nexplained as C/O cores experiencing unexpectedly rapid $^{22}$Ne sedimentation\nin the strongly liquid interior just prior to crystallization. We propose that\nthis rapid sedimentation is due to the formation of solid clusters of $^{22}$Ne\nin the liquid C/O background plasma. We show that these heavier solid clusters\nsink faster than individual $^{22}$Ne ions and enhance the sedimentation\nheating rate enough to dramatically slow WD cooling. MESA models including our\nprescription for cluster formation and sedimentation experience cooling delays\nof $\\approx$4 Gyr on the WD Q branch, alleviating tension between cooling ages\nand kinematic ages. This same model then predicts cooling delays coinciding\nwith crystallization of 6 Gyr or more in lower mass WDs (0.6-0.8 $M_\\odot$).\nSuch delays are compatible with, and perhaps required by, observations of WD\npopulations in the local 100 pc WD sample and the open cluster NGC 6791. These\nresults motivate new investigations of the physics of strongly coupled C/O/Ne\nplasma mixtures in the strongly liquid state near crystallization and tests\nthrough comparisons with observed WD cooling.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Sep 2020 23:10:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-21"}
